# Loading package
library(ggplot2)

# Creating a satterplot for two variables 'Sepal.Length' and 'Sepal.Width'
# Write your codes here
ggplot(data = newdata, 
       mapping = aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width)) + 
  geom_point()

# Adding another variable 'Species' and indicate 'Species' using color 
# Write your codes here
ggplot(data = newdata, 
       mapping = aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width, col = Species)) + 
  geom_point()

Q2. Please visualize the wt, hp, and am variables from the dataset mtcars by the scatterplot like below. Use the smooth method loess for wt and hp for different types of transmission (variable: am). Hint: \(col = factor(am)\):

# see more details about the dataset `mtcars` by using code: help(mtcars)
# write your answer here
# Loading data
data(mtcars)
newdata <- mtcars
# plot the data.
ggplot(data = newdata, 
       mapping = aes(x = wt, y = hp, col = factor(am))) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", formula = 'y ~ x')
